@node "Whatsit" "Whats it"
@next "Features"
@prev "Main"

 @{fg shine}Whats it?@{fg text}

 @{b}C/Log@{ub} is a last callers log & view program for CNet/3 & 4,
 with some blows and whistles like daily stats, flexible output and
 such. Read thru this document to get the idea.

 Over the years, quite some work went into this ARexx script, it runs
 on my BBS nearly ever since I'm online with CNet (which must've been
 sometime in 1994 or 1995 I think).
@endnode

@node "Features" "Features"
@next "Disclaimer"
@prev "Whatsit"

 @{fg shine}Features@{fg text}

 *   All the usual logging: login, handle, organization, time-on,
     up-size, down-size, baud etc.

 *   Logging of frontend connects (netcalls, frequests etc.) via
     aftersession part of ftn mailers. Also see @{"requirements" link "Requirements" 0}.

 *   Keeps track of DAILY calls/uploads/downloads, and yesterdays
     calls/uploads/downloads (no standard CNet information!)

 *   Keeps track of "all time highest" calls, files/bytes up,
     files/bytes down and written messages (all: feedback, mm, posts,
     responses, mail)

 *   Adapts to callers terminal height - huge display on huge terms!
     (sysop-definable maximum length).

 *   Logs mucho actions (Up/Down/Bulls/Doors/Chat/Carrier/Mail/Pubmail)

 *   Easy to add @{"own ansi/ascii" link "CFG_Logos" 0}, viewer module autochecks height of the
     ansi, so no need to fuzz around in my trashed ARexx script =)
@endnode

