 @{fg shine}Whodunnit?@{fg text}

 o  First version by @{b}Red Hawk@{ub}/Interactive

 o  Improved & bugfixed to "Acied Last" by @{b}Neurodancer@{ub}

 o  Improved to "1oo% Callerslog" by Neurodancer & @{b}Dreamer@{ub}

 o  Radical changes to "1oo% C/Log" by Neurodancer - check the history!

 Some words about me maybe? Well, I'm a 26 year old computer addict
 working in sales in my normal life. In my sparetime, besides
 maintaining my little BBS "Aurora Borealis" I do some music on the
 Amiga, maybe you stumbled across one or the other piece I've done.

 Concerning music, I love Goa/Psychedelic Trance, Ambient, Depeche
 Mode, Front 242, Sisters of Mercy, Fields of the Nephilim, Björk,
 Eternal Basement, Vangelis, the good old classic trance stuff as
 published by Eye Q and such...

 My BBS grew from a small system running on an unexpanded A2000 with
 a single v.32bis line to a two node 68040/33mhz system with v.34+
 and x.75; it also serves the small and nice "Coconet" to a couple
 of points and systems. The system is dedicated to the Amiga, CNet
 BBS, Modules, and ANSI/Ascii art.

 After german telekom changed their accounting, online activity
 dramatically dropped since most of my callers come from all across
 germany and are not on a cheap "local" range. New users are always
 very welcome, so don't bother to give me a call. :)
@endnode

@node "Contents" "Contents"
