 @{fg shine}Requirements@{fg text}

 o CNet BBS v3.05+   or   v4.xx

 o ARexx :)

 o "Getnode" from the TrapDoor distribution if you want to log netcalls
   (plus a TrapList compiled nodelist, of course)

 o An ANSI editor if you wanna make your own logos :)

 o An averagely developped brain for installation
@endnode

@node "Viewing" "viewing the log"
@next "Arguments"
@prev "Install_BBS"

 @{fg shine}Viewing the log@{fg text}

 To view the log, call "1oo_clog.rexx" with argument "VIEW" from
 anywhere you like (e.g. sys.welcome), put it to your GFiles/Bulls
 section, whatever.

 Example: {#0pfiles:1oo/clog/1oo_clog.rexx VIEW}
@endnode

@node "Arguments" "Arguments"
@next "Installation"
@prev "Viewing"
 
 @{fg shine}Arguments@{fg text}

 @{b}<none>@{ub}     without argument, C/Log will @{"update" link "Install_BBS" 0} the last callers list

 @{b}VIEW@{ub}       this argument will @{"view" link "Viewing" 0} the last callers log

 @{b}MAINT@{ub}      add C/Log with this argument as a bbscommand or into one of
            your pfile lists (preferably with maintenance access, hehe)
            to manually reset the daily statistics and add the @{"newday" link "CFG_Online" 18}
            divider (if enabled). Note that this is normally performed
            whenever the date has changed and C/Log is started (first
            call or view after midnight)

 @{b}NET@{ub}        starts C/Log's @{"netcall logging" link "Install_FTN" 0} routine, be sure to pass
            all necessary arguments together with this keyword!

 @{b}CONFIG@{ub}     runs C/Log's built-in @{"configuration" link "CFG_Online" 0} editor.
@endnode

